{
  "texts": [
    "This class of watermarking is used in different applications such as copyright protection, broadcast monitoring, copy control, and fingerprinting.",
    "If the embedded signature is lost or altered after the application of the host content, the watermarking is fragile.",
    "This class of watermarking is usually used for integrity verification and content authentication applications.",
    "The last type of watermarking is the semi-fragile class that is robust against some attacks, but it fails after malicious manipulations.",
    "This class can be used for image authentication applications.Bit error rate (BER) and normalized correlation (NC) are used to evaluate the robustness of a given watermarking."
  ]
}